I'll try to address aggro and DPS together.  We are not a DPS class (although some may argue that once we get all the offensive AA's we hold our own DPS wise). If you're not doing massive damage dont worry about it, just get and keep aggro.  Until you get to the level to get gear with nasty aggro procs, use the fastest weapons possible, and get some with procs that will actually activate at your level if you can.  (I remember vividly dual wielding dmg 3 dly 20 gnoll hide lariats at level 32 in crypt of dalnir.  The stun proc ruled at keeping aggro and interrupting all the @#!*@! casters in there).  Also, save taunt for when you need it, dont just mash the button every time it recycles.  Proximity is important, stand as close as you can to the mob you're fighting. Also, if you're fighting multiple mobs at once, have either the cleric or another class that can cast root root/park the extras off to the side (or if you're just fighting one, rooting it will guarantee that as long as the healers dont get close to it you'll keep aggro.)  Bottom line, managing aggro isnt just your job, it's your groups job.   I was dual wielding langseaxes and the best 2h weapon I had was a bronze 2h axe when I was lvl 20 (started in dec 1999), so I'd say you're ok gearwise, you just need to learn all the little tricks and nuances of aggro control.<br>
